Rating: 4
Easy and tasty. I used about a cup of sour cream, which I found easier to mix and spread than cream cheese. I also sliced the onion very thin and spread it on the crust with a little olive oil before baking, which worked nicely to tone down the onion flavor. I also skipped the lemon peel, used much more horseradish than called for and sprinkled about 2 tablespoons of capers on top.

