Rating: 3
I found this recipe to be very tasty. I used fat-free cream cheese and served it on round multi-grain crackers instead of pizza crust. Very tasty! I also used crumbled pieces of a whole smoked salmon that I received for Christmas instead of lox-style smoked salmon. That added extra texture.

Rating: 2
The flavour combination for this is exactly right, but I would not waste the wonderful ingredients on a plain old pizza base again. Lovely crackers or perhaps on a different, more flavourful flatbread of some sort (focaccia, etc) would prove a much better base for these lovely flavours. Do try the other ingredients-just don't waste it on a pizza base. (I would also recommend seasoning the cream cheese mixture with some fresh black pepper and some sea salt. Definitely developes the flavours better.)

